%
Human operators have dual roles: as producers of and as defenders against failure. - Richard I. Cook, MD. 'How Complex Systems Fail'.
%
All practitioner actions are gambles: acts that take place in the face of uncertain outcomes. - Richard I. Cook, MD. 'How Complex Systems Fail'.
%
Human practitioners are the adaptable element of complex systems. Some of these adaptations include: (1) Restructuring the system in order to reduce exposure of vulnerable parts to failure. (2) Concentrating critical resources in areas of expected high demand. (3) Providing pathways for retreat or recovery from expected and unexpected faults. (4) Establishing means for early detection of changed system performance in order to allow graceful cutbacks in production or other means of increasing resiliency. - Richard I. Cook, MD. 'How Complex Systems Fail'.
%
Human expertise in complex systems is constantly changing. - Richard I. Cook, MD. 'How Complex Systems Fail'.
