First Conundrum of the Universe: There's too much information. So we only notice changes, bizzareness, repetition, confirmation...
%
Second Conundrum of the Universe: There's not enough meaning. So we fill in gaps with patterns, generalities, benefit of doubt, easier problems, current mindset...
%
Third Conundrum of the Universe: There's not enough time and resources. So we assume we're right, we can do this, the nearest thing is best, we should finish what's started, we should keep our options open, easier is better...
%
Fourth Conundrum of the Universe: There's not enough memory. So we save space by editing memories down, generalizing, keeping an example, using external memory...
