%
Customer Obsession: Start with the customer and work backwards. Work vigorously to earn and keep customer trust. Pay attention to competitors, but obsess over customers. - Amazon leadership principle
%
Ownership: Think long term and don't sacrifice long-term value for short-term results. Act on behalf of the entire company, beyond just your own team. Never say "that's not my job." - Amazon leadership principle
%
Invent and Simplify: Expect and require innovation and invention from your teams and always find ways to simplify. Be externally aware, look for new ideas from everywhere, and don't be limited by "not invented here." As we do new things, we accept that we may be misunderstood for long periods of time. - Amazon leadership principle
%
Right, A Lot: Have strong judgment and good instincts, seek diverse perspectives and work to disconfirm your beliefs. - Amazon leadership principle
%
Learn and Be Curious: You are never done learning. Always seek to improve yourself. Be curious about new possibilities and act to explore them. - Amazon leadership principle
%
Hire and Develop the Best: Raise the performance bar with every hire and promotion. Recognize exceptional talent, and willingly move them throughout the organization. Develop leaders and take seriously their role in coaching others. Work on behalf of others to invent mechanisms for development. - Amazon leadership principle
%
Insist on the Highest Standards: Relentlessly high standards — many people may think these standards are unreasonably high. Continually raise the bar and drive teams to deliver high quality products, services, and processes. Ensure that defects do not get sent down the line and that problems are fixed so they stay fixed. - Amazon leadership principle
%
Think Big: Thinking small is a self-fulfilling prophecy. Create and communicate a bold direction that inspires results. Think differently and look around corners for ways to serve customers. - Amazon leadership principle
%
Bias for Action: Speed matters. Many decisions and actions are reversible and do not need extensive study. Value calculated risk taking. - Amazon leadership principle
%
Frugality: Accomplish more with less. Constraints breed resourcefulness, self-sufficiency, and invention. No extra points for growing headcount, budget size, or fixed expense. - Amazon leadership principle
%
Earn Trust: Listen attentively, speak candidly, and treat others respectfully. Be vocally self-critical, even when doing so is awkward or embarrassing. Benchmark yourself and your teams against the best. - Amazon leadership principle
%
Dive Deep: Operate at all levels, stay connected to the details, audit frequently, and be skeptical when metrics and anecdote differ. No task is beneath you. - Amazon leadership principle
%
Have Backbone; Disagree and Commit: Respectfully challenge decisions when you disagree, even when doing so is uncomfortable or exhausting. Have conviction and be tenacious. Do not compromise for the sake of social cohesion. Once a decision is determined, commit wholly. - Amazon leadership principle
%
Deliver Results: Focus on key inputs and deliver them with quality and timeliness. Despite setbacks, rise to the occasion and never settle. - Amazon leadership principle
